      <p>Always inspiring, Joe would greet everyone with a genuine smile. His response to the usual greeting, “Have a good day” was always “Might as well” because always given the choice, Joe chose the good day. In his most challenging times, he was reaching out to others. His attention to all matters, be it others with Glioblastoma Multiforme and their caregivers to general questions of carpentry and life, was as impeccable as his craftsmanship.</p>
